        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "build(pnpm): bump pnpm to 11.2.2 & use packageManager as pnpm source",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nBumps pnpm to `11.2.2` and makes CI/release workflows use the repo's `packageManager` pin instead of separate hardcoded pnpm versions.\n\n## Changed\n\n- Updated the root `packageManager` pin to pnpm `11.2.2`.\n- Removed workflow-level `PNPM_VERSION` constants and `pnpm-version` plumbing from CI/release workflows.\n- Updated the shared pnpm setup action to resolve pnpm from `package.json#packageManager` by default, with an explicit override still available.\n- Added workflow tests to keep pnpm version selection centralized.\n\n## Risks\n\nThe branch is blocked until current lockfile entries age past the repo's `minimumReleaseAge: 2880` policy. Newer pnpm validates existing lockfile entries too, and several dependency updates currently in `pnpm-lock.yaml` are still less than 48 hours old.\n\nReferences:\n- https://github.com/orgs/pnpm/discussions/11377\n- https://pnpm.io/settings#minimumreleaseage\n- https://github.com/pnpm/pnpm/releases/tag/v11.1.3\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `actionlint` on touched workflow files\n- Cloudflare Crabbox focused workflow tests passed with `--config.minimum-release-age=0` after confirming the default install failure is the known release-age policy gate.\n\n## Complexity\n\nReduced: pnpm version selection now has one source of truth in `package.json#packageManager`; workflows no longer carry separate pnpm pins.\n",
        "branch": "feat/pnpm-11.2.2",
